SLS 26RS-4615 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 196
BY SENATOR BARROW
BLIGHTED PROPERTY. Creates a statewide taskforce to study and make
recommendations on implementing a comprehensive plan to address property blight within
the state.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To create and provide for the Task Force on Blight to study and make recommendations on
3 implementing a comprehensive plan to address property blight within the state.
4 WHEREAS, dilapidated properties and overgrown lots, otherwise known as blight,
5 have long been among the parishes' and municipalities' most vexing challenges; and
6 WHEREAS, over the last forty years the legislature has sought ways to address blight
7 across the state by enacting several statutes; and
8 WHEREAS, in the 1980s, the legislature sought to address blight by enacting Act
9 571 of the 1984 Regular Session which is referred to as the Urban Land-Banking Law; and
10 WHEREAS, under the Urban Land-Banking Law the legislature's findings and
11 declaration state in part that "[t]here exist in many cities of the state economically and
12 physically depressed residential neighborhood areas which, among other things, suffer from
13 high unemployment, substandard and deteriorated structures, vacant and partially used lots,
14 overcrowded housing, high crime rates, and other blighting influences and undesirable
15 conditions"; and
16 WHEREAS, in the 1990s, the legislature enacted the Slum Clearance Law as Act
17 1188 of the 1997 Regular Session authorizing municipalities to tackle slum conditions in a
18 just and legal way; and
