1 WHEREAS, a portion of the Slum Clearance Law states "[w]henever any
2 municipality finds that there exists within it dwellings which are unfit for human habitation
3 due to dilapidation; defects increasing the hazards of fires, accidents, or other calamities;
4 lack of ventilation, light, or sanitary facilities, or other conditions rendering the dwellings
5 unsafe and unsanitary and dangerous or detrimental to health, safety, or morals, or that there
6 are dwellings therein which are otherwise inimical to the welfare of its residents, it may
7 exercise its police powers to remedy or eliminate those conditions in the manner provided
8 in this Part"; and
9 WHEREAS, in the 2000s, the legislature enacted the Louisiana Housing Preservation
10 Act as Act 355 of the 2006 Regular Session to address blighted and abandoned residential
11 housing properties by authorizing the creation of a "blighted property list" which is prepared
12 and periodically updated by a designated public official that identifies blighted housing
13 properties in the jurisdiction of the local governmental subdivision; and
14 WHEREAS, the legislature seeks to address property blight by studying and
15 reviewing comprehensive plans to eradicate blight in Louisiana.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
17 does hereby establish and provide for the Task Force on Blight to study implementing a
18 comprehensive plan to address property blight within the state, and to propose
19 recommendations, together with specific proposals for legislation, by written report to the
20 legislature and to the David R. Poynter Legislative Research Library as required by R.S.
21 24:771 and 772, no later than March 1, 2027.
22 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force should include consideration of
23 the following:
24 (1) A strategic plan to abate blight within the state.
25 (2) Use of data-driven decision-making.
26 (3) Strategic deployment of resources and place-based revitalization.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall consist of the following
28 members:
29 (1) The president of the Senate or his designee, who shall serve as the chairman of
30 the task force.
